Package fr.inria.boreal.jfbaget.irirefs.managers

Record Class AbstractIRIManager.PrefixedIRI

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
fr.inria.boreal.jfbaget.irirefs.managers.AbstractIRIManager.PrefixedIRI
Record Components:
prefix - the identifier associated with a base IRI (must be registered in the manager)
iri - the relative or absolute IRIRef to resolve against the prefix base
Enclosing class:
AbstractIRIManager
protected static record AbstractIRIManager.PrefixedIRI(String prefix, IRIRef iri) extends Record
Represents a prefix-IRI pair used for resolution or registration.

This record bundles a prefix (e.g., "ex") with an IRIRef that is intended to be resolved using the IRI base associated with the prefix. Commonly used in prefixed notations such as ex:foo.

    • PrefixedIRI

      public PrefixedIRI(String prefix, String iri) throws IRIParseException
      Constructs a PrefixedIRI from a string representation of the IRIRef.

      This is a convenience constructor that internally parses the iriString into an IRIRef object.

      Parameters:
      prefix - the prefix to use (e.g., "ex")
      iriString - the string representation of the IRIRef to associate with the prefix
      Throws:
      IRIParseException - if the iriString is not a valid IRIRef
